cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.DL, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with the organization and retrieval of information using metadata. It could also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category as it focuses on social metadata and community organization of knowledge. Additionally, it could be classified under the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category as it proposes an approach to folksonomy learning. The sub-categories of Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Databases (cs.DB) are less likely as they are not directly related to the topic of the paper.
